SIMPLE: grounding
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grounding
<hw>Ground"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act, method, or
process of laying a groundwork or foundation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <ety>[Nominalized form of
<er>ground</er>{3}, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>Elementary instruction;
instruction in the basic concepts of a topic or skill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The act or process of applying a ground, as of
color, to wall paper, cotton cloth, etc.; a basis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Groundless</ent>⟦br⟧
